      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "PURPLE PRINCE (6) on the quick back-up after he surged late in the heavy (10) going with an eye-catching third over 1614m at Taree. Placed at this trip and can finally get his Maiden win out of the way. GRANDE DIABLO (1) lightly raced three-year-old who finds a winnable contest today. Drifted back early and covered ground in the run with a plugging sixth over 1750m at Muswellbrook. This looks much easier with the senior rider going on. Among the leading chances. HEAPY'S LEGACY (2) stretches out to this trip for the first time and should be at his top for this fifth-up. Warmed up late when sixth over 1600m at Quirindi. Expected to show a bit more today. MINISTER GARRETT (5) visors come off for this after he worked himself back into form with a close-up second over 2000m at Quirindi. Will roll forward again and figure prominently.",
